 JANUS Research Group is seeking a Chief Scientist with research, development, and testing experience in Aberdeen Proving Ground, MD. This candidate will be responsible for leading a team conducting research and studies of complex problems in Multi-Domain Operations, and providing the basis for highly available, reliable, and scalable solutions. 
 Your Future Duties And Responsibilities: 
 Lead the design and development underlying architecture and interfaces for Identity Intelligence products. 
 Oversee development of processes, models, and tools to analyze collection data and apply modern Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence techniques. 
 Identify and leverage leading edge technologies and innovative enterprise solutions to increase operation flexibility and agility. 
 Modeling and Simulation for system development, prototyping, integration, and deployment. 
 
 Experience and Education 
 Required Skills: 
 The candidate shall have an active DoD TS/SCI clearance. 
 Must work well in agile team environments. 
 Atlassian Suite of tools (JIRA, Confluence). 
 MS Office Suite of tools. 
 Leading large technical teams. 
 
